Description: For sale is a Fender Stratocaster Plus Model 10-9500 purchased new in 1994. Fender/Lace Sensor pickups (blue, silver, red), Fender/Wilkinson roller nut, Deluxe American Standard tremolo. Hip-Shot Trem-Setter tremolo stabilizer. Made in USA. 6.93 pounds. Very good if not excellent condition. Close inspection reveals some pick guard scratching, and barely visible surficial scratches above the pick guard and elsewhere. The scratches won’t show in pictures. There is a small chip in the paint near the neck joint (pictured). Slight visible fret wear that will disappear with light polishing. The guitar has been set up using mechanical basics: spring deflection measurements, string height and spring distance measurements, and string tension specs (pictured). Like Leo must have done it 70 years ago. The bridge plate is parallel to the face, so minimal upward tremolo bending, but it now stays in tune better than my fixed bridge guitars. All original except for hex-head 1.5” and 2” #10 tremolo claw screws. These make tension fine adjustment much easier. The original 1.5” #10 Phillips head screws are included. Includes original case candy, manual, tags, hex keys, strap locks, tremolo bar, and strap. Fender Plus hard-shell case is in good shape but for 4 collapsed feet. It went through airport baggage a few times. Ships to a verifiable address CONUS only.
Title: Fender American Stratocaster Plus 1994
